-- U.S. Stocks Pare Gains as Consumer Confidence Offsets Bernanke's Remarks
-- B y   N i c k   B a k e r
-- 2010-10-15T13:57:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/u-s-stocks-pare-gains-as-consumer-confidence-offsets-bernanke-s-remarks.html
U.S. stocks pared gains after a
measure of consumer confidence trailed estimates, offsetting
optimism that lower-than-estimated inflation data bolstered
Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke ’s case that more
monetary stimulus may be needed to safeguard the economy.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index rose 0.2 percent to
1,176.51 at 9:56 a.m. in New York after climbing 0.6 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
